of crisis mappers he serves on the boards of the meta activism project map and digital democracy patrick was previously the co director of the harvard humanitarian initiative's hhi program on crisis mapping and early warning he has consulted for several international organizations on numerous crisis mapping and early warning projects in africa asia and europe patrick is completing his phd at the fletcher school of law and diplomacy at tufts university his dissertation focuses on the the impact of information and communication technologies on the balance of power between repressive regimes and popular movements he has an ma in international affairs from columbia university and is an alum of the sante fe institute's sfi complex systems summer school downloads audio audio talk and q&a session streaming mp3 location encina ground floor conference room encina hall 616 serra st e008 ground floor stanford university stanford ca 94305 directions map fsi contact audrey mcgowan topics democracy diplomacy disaster response governance human rights liberation technology organizations egypt europe haiti kenya sudan search cddrl search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages events of interest liberation technology in authoritarian regimes conference pdf+ word doc+ cancelled tavneet suri liberation technology seminar series tavneet suri liberation technology introduction to series vivek srinivasan the impact of technology access on protest frequency in authoritarian regimes patrick meier video+ pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4610 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
